						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone lying in front of the temple of Chennakēśava</hi></p>						

						<p>Vikramāditya II—A.D. 1191-92.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged inscription refers itself to the rule of a <hi rend="bold">Gutta</hi> chief (name lost) and is dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka [1]114, Virōdhikṛit, Monday.</hi> Other details are lost. The Śaka year cited corresponds to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1191-92.</hi> On the strength of the date the record may be ascribed to <hi rend="bold">Vikramāditya II.</hi> It seems to record the death of <hi rend="bold">Bamaya-Nāyaka</hi> in a fight. <hi rend="bold">Guttavoḷal</hi> is mentioned.</p>						

						</summary>
